# writableTypes

**Type Property**

Returns the types of data the receiver can write natively and any types filterable to that native type.

## Declaration

```swift
@MainActor class var writableTypes: [String] { get }
```

## Return Value

An array of `NSString` objects representing the writable document types.

## Managing File Type Information

- **readableTypes**: Returns the types of data the receiver can read natively and any types filterable to that native type.
- **isNativeType(_:)**: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the document can read and write the data natively.
- **writableTypes(for:)**: Returns the names of the types to which this document can be saved for a specified kind of save operation.
- **fileNameExtension(forType:saveOperation:)**: Returns a filename extension that can be appended to a base filename, for a specified file type and kind of save operation.
